        <p>LEAD: To the Editor:</p>
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Of today's sources of electricity, nuclear energy is most appropriate for combating the greenhouse effect because it is the only large-scale energy source - except falling water - that produces no harmful greenhouse gases.  J. CORDNER GIBSON  Citizens for Adequate Energy,  San Luis Obispo, Calif., Sept. 5</p>
